You are Cursor acting as a senior full-stack engineer. Build a SUBCONTRACTOR PORTAL MVP for BLVCKSHELL Facilities Services.

GOAL
A subcontractor-only portal that answers:
1) Where do I go?
2) When do I go?
3) What exactly do I do there?
4) How do I prove completion so I get paid?

HARD SCOPE LIMITS (DO NOT DRIFT)
- ONLY subcontractor portal + minimal admin approval. NO client portal.
- NO automated payments, NO reporting dashboards, NO SLA timers, NO multi-org complexity.
- NO KPI dashboards or metrics visualization in Phase 1. Data is collected for audit/compliance but NOT visualized.
- Keep it simple, production-safe, deterministic, and auditable.

TECH STACK (use exactly this unless already present)
- Next.js 14+ App Router (TypeScript)
- Postgres
- Prisma ORM
- Auth: NextAuth (Credentials provider) OR custom JWT if simpler, but must be secure.
- File storage: local dev file system for MVP + interface layer so we can swap to S3 later.
- Styling: Tailwind (clean, minimal, professional). No fancy UI libraries.

MULTI-TENANCY
- Single company (BLVCKSHELL) for MVP.
- Users have roles: ADMIN or SUBCONTRACTOR.
- SUBCONTRACTOR sees only their assigned jobs.
- ADMIN can manage sites, scopes/checklists, assign jobs, approve completion, mark payouts.

CORE ENTITIES (Prisma models)
Create Prisma models (with proper relations, indexes) for:
- User (id, email, passwordHash, role, name, phone, isActive, createdAt)
- Site (id, name, addressLine1, city, province, postalCode, accessInstructions, notes, isActive)
- ChecklistTemplate (id, siteId, title, items[], isActive, version, createdAt)  // items stored as JSON array with stable itemIds
- Job (id, siteId, assignedToUserId, scheduledStart, scheduledEnd, status, payoutAmountCents, createdAt)
- JobCompletion (id, jobId, completedByUserId, completedAt, checklistResults JSON, notes)
- Evidence (id, jobCompletionId, filePath, fileType, uploadedAt)
- Approval (id, jobId, approvedByUserId, approvedAt, decision, notes)
- PayoutBatch (id, periodStart, periodEnd, status, createdAt)
- PayoutLine (id, payoutBatchId, userId, jobId, amountCents, status)

STATE MACHINES (ENFORCE THESE IN CODE)
Job.status enum:
- SCHEDULED
- COMPLETED_PENDING_APPROVAL
- APPROVED_PAYABLE
- PAID
- CANCELLED

Rules:
- Only SUBCONTRACTOR can move SCHEDULED -> COMPLETED_PENDING_APPROVAL by submitting completion.
- Completion submission requires: all checklist items answered + minimum photo evidence count (configurable per site, default 4).
- Only ADMIN can approve: COMPLETED_PENDING_APPROVAL -> APPROVED_PAYABLE.
- Only ADMIN can mark paid: APPROVED_PAYABLE -> PAID (via payout batch).
- Every state transition must be written to an AuditLog table (add this model) with: actorUserId, entityType, entityId, fromState, toState, metadata JSON, createdAt.

PAGES / UX (App Router)
Subcontractor pages:
- /login
- /jobs (list upcoming + past, with status chips)
- /jobs/[id] (job detail: site info, access instructions, checklist, evidence uploader, submit completion)
- /earnings (list jobs and payout status; show totals for current period)

Admin pages (simple, not pretty, but usable):
- /admin/sites (CRUD)
- /admin/sites/[id]/checklists (manage checklist template versions + required photo count per site)
- /admin/jobs (create jobs, assign to subcontractors, calendar-lite list view)
- /admin/jobs/[id] (review completion, photos, approve/reject with notes)
- /admin/payouts (create payout batch for a date range; include approved jobs; mark paid)

CHECKLIST & EVIDENCE
- Each Site has a requiredPhotoCount integer.
- Checklist items must be stable (each item has itemId + label).
- Completion stores results as JSON keyed by itemId with values: PASS/FAIL/NA + optional note.
- Evidence uploader must support multiple images, store them, and associate them to completion.
- Show thumbnails in review.

SECURITY REQUIREMENTS (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
- Passwords hashed with bcrypt.
- RBAC enforced server-side on every route/action.
- Prevent IDOR: a subcontractor must never access another subcontractor’s job.
- CSRF protection if using NextAuth.
- Validate all inputs with zod.
- Use server actions or API routes with strict validation; no direct client DB access.

DATA SEEDING
- Provide a seed script that creates:
  - 1 admin user
  - 2 subcontractor users
  - 2 sites with checklists
  - 6 jobs assigned across subs

DELIVERABLES
1) Working app with the routes above
2) Prisma schema + migrations
3) Seed script + README with setup steps
4) Clean code, no placeholders, no TODOs for core flows
5) Unit tests for state transitions + RBAC checks (minimal but real)

BUILD ORDER
1) Setup Next.js + Tailwind + Prisma + Auth
2) Prisma models + migrations + seed
3) Subcontractor job list/detail + completion submission (checklist + photos)
4) Admin review + approve/reject
5) Payout batch + mark paid
6) Audit log + tests

IMPORTANT
- Do not add features outside scope.
- If any requirement is ambiguous, make the simplest reasonable choice and document it in README.
- Keep UI clean and professional (BLVCKSHELL vibe: dark/neutral, but do not overdesign).


