prompt 1 (REVISED) — Workforce Operations Portal (MODIFY & FINALIZE)
Use this spec to modify and finalize the existing Subcontractor Portal. This supersedes the original Prompt 1 for implementation. Not greenfield; required adjustments and expansions only. No UX redesign unless required.

You are Cursor acting as a PRINCIPAL FULL-STACK ENGINEER and OPERATIONS ARCHITECT. MODIFY AND FINALIZE the existing Subcontractor Portal MVP for BLVCKSHELL Facilities Services so it is production-safe, scalable, and operationally correct.

CORE GOAL
Build a WORKFORCE-DRIVEN OPERATIONS PORTAL that supports:
• Vendor subcontractors with MULTIPLE EMPLOYEES (teams)
• Internal BLVCKSHELL employees
• Admin-controlled job assignment, approval, and payout
• Deterministic state machines
• Audit-safe evidence collection
• Compliance enforcement
• Supabase + Prisma + Vercel correctness

System must survive audits, disputes, staff turnover, and growth.

TECH STACK (LOCKED)
• Next.js 14+ App Router (TypeScript)
• Prisma ORM
• Supabase Postgres
• Supabase Storage (MANDATORY — no local filesystem)
• Vercel deployment
• Auth: NextAuth Credentials OR custom JWT (bcrypt required)
• Tailwind CSS (clean, minimal)

DATABASE CONNECTION RULES:
• Use Supabase pooled DATABASE_URL for runtime
• Use DIRECT_URL for Prisma migrations
• Document this clearly in README

ABSOLUTE CONSTRAINTS
• NO client portal
• NO automated payments
• NO reporting dashboards or KPI visualization (Phase 1)
• NO scope creep
• NO hourly billing logic
• NO filesystem storage
• NO soft state transitions
• ALL permissions enforced server-side
• ALL state transitions audit logged
• EVERYTHING deterministic
• Metrics collected but NOT visualized: missed visits, recleans, time-to-approval, vendor incident rate (see ROADMAP.md Part 8)

If ambiguous, choose the SIMPLEST defensible option and document in DECISIONS.md.

REQUIRED CORE MODELS (PRISMA)

1) ClientOrganization (minimal, future-proof)
- id, name, primaryContactName, primaryContactEmail, primaryContactPhone, notes, createdAt

2) WorkforceAccount
- type enum: INTERNAL | VENDOR
- id, type, displayName, legalName (nullable), primaryContactName, primaryContactEmail, primaryContactPhone, hstNumber (nullable), wsibAccountNumber (nullable), isActive, createdAt, updatedAt

3) User (auth)
- id, email (unique), passwordHash, role enum: ADMIN | VENDOR_OWNER | VENDOR_WORKER | INTERNAL_WORKER, workforceAccountId (nullable for ADMIN), name, phone, isActive, createdAt

4) Worker (operational identity)
- id, userId (unique), workforceAccountId, hasPhotoIdOnFile (bool), isActive, createdAt, updatedAt

5) ComplianceDocument (Supabase Storage)
- type enum: COI | WSIB | AGREEMENT | HST | OTHER
- id, workforceAccountId, type, storagePath, expiresAt (nullable), uploadedAt
- RULE: Expired or missing COI/WSIB blocks new job assignment unless ADMIN override (audit logged).

6) Site
- id, clientOrganizationId, name, address, accessInstructions, serviceWindow, estimatedDurationMinutes, requiredPhotoCount (default 4), suppliesProvidedBy enum: COMPANY | CLIENT | MIXED, doNotEnterUnits (bool), isActive

7) AccessCredential (key/FOB/code ledger)
- id, siteId, type enum: KEY | FOB | CODE, identifier (masked if code), issuedToWorkerId, issuedAt, returnedAt (nullable), status enum: ACTIVE | LOST | RETURNED, notes
- Lost credentials must trigger IncidentReport.

8) ChecklistTemplate
- id, siteId, version, isActive, items JSON (stable itemId required), createdAt

9) Job
- status enum: SCHEDULED | COMPLETED_PENDING_APPROVAL | APPROVED_PAYABLE | PAID | CANCELLED
- id, siteId, scheduledStart, scheduledEnd, status, payoutAmountCents, assignedWorkforceAccountId (nullable), assignedWorkerId (nullable), isMissed (bool), missedReason (nullable), makeGoodJobId (nullable), createdAt
- RULE: Exactly ONE of assignedWorkforceAccountId OR assignedWorkerId must be set.

10) JobCompletion
- id, jobId (unique, 1:1), completedByWorkerId, completedAt, checklistResults JSON, notes

11) Evidence (Supabase Storage)
- id, jobCompletionId, storagePath, fileType, uploadedAt

12) WorkOrder (change order / add-on)
- id, siteId, requestedBy, description, approvedByAdminId, priceCents, status enum: REQUESTED | APPROVED | ASSIGNED | COMPLETED | INVOICED | PAID, beforePhotos (optional), afterPhotos (optional)

13) IncidentReport
- type enum: SAFETY | PROPERTY_DAMAGE | BIOHAZARD | LOST_KEY | OTHER
- id, siteId, workerId, description, photos, reportedAt, resolvedAt (nullable), resolutionNotes

14) PayoutBatch / PayoutLine
- Payouts go to WorkforceAccount. Worker reference optional for reporting.

15) AuditLog (MANDATORY)
- id, actorUserId, actorWorkerId (nullable), actorWorkforceAccountId (nullable), entityType, entityId, fromState, toState, metadata JSON, createdAt

STATE MACHINES (ENFORCE IN CODE)

Job:
• SCHEDULED → COMPLETED_PENDING_APPROVAL (Worker only; checklist + photos required)
• COMPLETED_PENDING_APPROVAL → APPROVED_PAYABLE (ADMIN only)
• COMPLETED_PENDING_APPROVAL → SCHEDULED (ADMIN reject; rejection reason required)
• SCHEDULED or COMPLETED_PENDING_APPROVAL → CANCELLED (ADMIN only)
• APPROVED_PAYABLE → PAID (ADMIN only via payout batch)
Missed visit: mark job isMissed=true; create make-good Job linked via makeGoodJobId.
NO other Job transitions allowed. ALL transitions write AuditLog.

RBAC (NON-NEGOTIABLE, SERVER-SIDE)
ADMIN: Full access; workforce + worker management; compliance enforcement; job assignment/reassignment; approvals; payouts; overrides.
VENDOR_OWNER: Manage workers in own WorkforceAccount; view vendor-assigned jobs; NO pricing visibility; NO approvals; NO payouts.
VENDOR_WORKER / INTERNAL_WORKER: View only assigned jobs; submit completion proof; view earnings (read-only).

REQUIRED SCREENS

ADMIN: /admin/workforce, /admin/workforce/[id], /admin/jobs, /admin/jobs/[id], /admin/workorders, /admin/incidents, /admin/payouts
WORKERS: /jobs, /jobs/[id], /earnings, /profile
VENDOR OWNER (scaffold): /vendor/team, /vendor/jobs

FILE UPLOAD (SUPABASE STORAGE)
• jpg, jpeg, png, webp only; max 10MB
• Path: evidence/{jobId}/{completionId}/{timestamp}-{uuid}.{ext}
• Server-side validation; reject completion if photo minimum not met
• Retention: 90 days default (manual purge OK); document in DATA_RETENTION.md

REQUIRED DOCUMENTATION
• README.md (setup + deploy; DATABASE_URL vs DIRECT_URL)
• DECISIONS.md (explicit product decisions)
• SECURITY.md (RBAC + data handling)
• DATA_RETENTION.md
• SEED.md (seed instructions)

SEED DATA (MUST INCLUDE)
• 1 admin
• 1 vendor workforce with 2 workers
• 1 internal workforce with 1 worker
• 2 client orgs
• 2 sites
• 6 jobs (mixed assignments)
• 1 missed visit + make-good job
• 1 work order
• 1 incident

PRODUCTION READINESS (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
Implement these so the portal survives real ops and security scrutiny. Do not ship without them.

Security hardening
• Rate limit: login, job completion submission, and evidence upload endpoints (per-IP or per-user); document in SECURITY.md.
• Session: timeout and refresh strategy (e.g. 24h max, refresh on activity); document in SECURITY.md.
• Login backoff / lockout: after N failed attempts (e.g. 5), temporary backoff or lockout; document in SECURITY.md.
• Password reset: no self-serve in MVP; admin can reset user password (audit logged). See DECISIONS.md.

Data integrity
• Deletion: prefer RESTRICT on FKs for Job, JobCompletion, Evidence, AuditLog; soft-deactivate (isActive = false) for User, WorkforceAccount, Site; document cascade/restrict in schema and DECISIONS.md.
• Uniques: User.email; JobCompletion.jobId (1:1 with Job); one active ChecklistTemplate per site per version (document and enforce).
• completedByWorkerId: allowed when job is assigned to WorkforceAccount (any worker from that account may complete); document in DECISIONS.md.

UX reliability (operational failure handling)
• Upload retry + draft: allow retry on failed uploads; support saving partial completion (draft) so worker can resume without losing work.
• Validation errors: clear inline errors for missing required photos, missing checklist items, wrong file type/size before submit.
• Mobile-first completion: job completion flow must work on mobile; camera upload for evidence; touch-friendly checklist and submit.

Decision locks (must be in DECISIONS.md)
• Evidence retention window (e.g. 90 days) and purge process.
• Compliance gating: expired/missing COI/WSIB blocks new assignment; ADMIN override only with audit log (metadata: reason, overrideAt).
• Access credential masking: codes masked in UI (e.g. last 4); full value only to authorized roles; document in SECURITY.md.
• Max photos per job: cap (e.g. 20); enforce in UI (disable past cap) and server (reject upload and completion over cap).
• Vendor owner job reassignment: Phase 1 = No; only ADMIN assigns/reassigns jobs.
• Final implementation locks (DECISIONS.md): Supabase Storage security (server-only service role vs signed URLs—choose one); draft completion model (JobCompletionDraft table OR JobCompletion DRAFT status; define if photos attach to drafts); workforce-assigned job visibility (Phase 1: job shown to workers only when assignedWorkerId set by admin—do not show to whole team until claimed/assigned); max photo cap enforced UI + server; password reset = admin-initiated only, audit logged.

Testing bar (explicit suite)
• Unit: all allowed and denied state transitions per role (Job and WorkOrder); explicit cases, not "minimal."
• RBAC/IDOR: attempts to access another user's job, completion, evidence, work order, incident must return 403; cover all five.
• Storage/upload: reject disallowed MIME and oversize; assert no file stored.
• One E2E: assign → complete (checklist + photos) → approve → payout batch → mark paid.

IMPORTANT
• No TODOs in core logic
• No fake flows
• No redesign unless required
• Prefer auditability > correctness > simplicity > speed
• Build boring, defensible software
• Do not treat as production-ready until all PRODUCTION READINESS items above are implemented and documented


