prompt 3
You are Cursor acting as a principal operations architect and senior technical writer. Your job is to produce a Tier-1 "Operations Binder" for BLVCKSHELL Facilities Services (Ontario, Canada): contracts, SOPs, policies, QA forms, and supporting checklists. This binder must be immediately usable to run condo + rental/common-area cleaning with subcontractors, and must be structured so it can be loaded into a portal later (site templates, checklists, forms, and state workflows).

ABSOLUTE CONSTRAINTS
- Do not invent legal advice; draft "commercially standard" agreements and include a "review by Ontario counsel recommended" note.
- No placeholders like "TBD" for core content. Where details vary by site, use explicit bracket fields (e.g., [SITE NAME], [FREQUENCY], [REQUIRED PHOTO COUNT]).
- No generic fluff. Every section must be actionable: procedures, decision rules, acceptance criteria, and evidence requirements.
- Keep everything deterministic: define "done," "pass/fail," and "who decides."
- Use clear Ontario/Canada terms: HST, WSIB, COI (Certificate of Insurance), etc.

DELIVERABLE FORMAT
Create a folder-style output in Markdown with separate files (show content for each file). Use this exact structure:

/ops-binder/
  00_README.md
  01_Client_Contract/
    01_Master_Service_Agreement.md
    02_Schedule_A_Site_Scope_Template.md
    03_Schedule_B_Add_On_Menu_and_Pricing_Template.md
    04_Schedule_C_Access_And_Site_Rules_Template.md
    05_Schedule_D_QA_And_Evidence_Requirements.md
    06_Schedule_E_Insurance_Compliance.md
    07_Work_Order_Change_Order_Template.md
    08_Credit_And_Reclean_Policy_Addendum.md
  02_Subcontractor_Contract/
    01_Independent_Subcontractor_Agreement_Longform.md
    02_Subcontractor_One_Page_Summary.md
    03_Rate_Sheet_Template.md
    04_Sub_Scope_Will_Wont_Do.md
    05_Sub_Onboarding_Checklist.md
  03_SOPs/
    SOP_01_Common_Area_Cleaning.md
    SOP_02_Site_Access_And_Conduct.md
    SOP_03_Completion_Proof_And_Submission.md
    SOP_04_Issue_Escalation_And_Incident_Response.md
    SOP_05_Add_On_Services_Execution.md
    SOP_06_Light_Maintenance_Scope_And_Workflow.md
  04_Policies/
    POL_01_Quality_Standard_and_Rework.md
    POL_02_Health_Safety_and_PPE.md
    POL_03_Privacy_Photo_Handling_and_Data.md
    POL_04_Subcontractor_Conduct_and_NonSolicit.md
