  06_Checklists_Library/
    CL_01_Lobby_Checklist.md
    CL_02_Hallway_Checklist.md
    CL_03_Stairwell_Checklist.md
    CL_04_Elevator_Checklist.md
    CL_05_Garbage_Room_Checklist.md
    CL_06_Glass_Doors_Spot_Checklist.md
    CL_07_Washroom_Common_Area_Checklist.md
    CL_08_Seasonal_Deep_Clean_Checklist.md
  07_State_Machines_and_Roles/
    01_Roles_and_RBAC.md
    02_State_Machines_Jobs_WorkOrders_Invoices_Payouts.md
    03_Audit_Log_Requirements.md
  08_Sales_Enablement/
    01_Discovery_Call_Script_Property_Managers.md
    02_Site_Walk_Checklist.md
    03_Proposal_Insert_QA_and_Accountability.md

CONTENT REQUIREMENTS (EXTREME DETAIL)

A) MASTER SERVICE AGREEMENT (Client)
- Must define: parties, term, scope by schedules, frequency, service windows, client responsibilities, access, security, payment terms (monthly in advance; add-ons separate), HST, late fees policy (optional), service holds for non-payment, termination (30–60 days), limitation of liability, indemnity, force majeure, confidentiality, privacy, governing law Ontario, notices, entire agreement.
- Must explicitly state: "Company does not perform licensed trades; coordinates third parties if requested" unless a separate agreement exists.
- Must include "No hourly billing; flat monthly fee for scheduled services."

B) SCHEDULES
Schedule A: Site Scope Template
- For each area: include/exclude list + frequency + acceptance criteria ("no visible debris," "glass streak-free," "garbage room floors free of residue," etc.)
Schedule B: Add-on Menu Template
- Define each add-on with: included tasks, exclusions, pricing field, emergency surcharge rules, approval requirement.
Schedule C: Access & Site Rules
- Keys, FOBs, codes; lost key penalties; concierge instructions; parking; service windows; noise rules.
Schedule D: QA & Evidence
- Required photo count per visit; required photo locations; inspection cadence; re-clean policy reference.
Schedule E: Insurance/Compliance
- COI requirements, WSIB, HST number, additional insured wording, incident reporting timelines.

C) SUBCONTRACTOR AGREEMENT LONGFORM
- Must include: independent contractor status, confidentiality, non-solicit/non-circumvention (24 months), standards, photo proof requirement, payment terms (per job; only approved), right to withhold for deficiencies, termination for cause, indemnity, governing law Ontario, tools/supplies expectations, no client contact rule.
- Must include a remedies section for solicitation breach: injunctive relief + liquidated damages clause (careful: define a reasonable amount per client/site) and explain it as a genuine pre-estimate.
- Must avoid illegal non-compete; keep it to non-solicit/non-circumvent and confidentiality.

D) RATE SHEET TEMPLATE
- Provide a structured table:
  - Per-visit rates by property type (small condo / medium / large)
  - Add-on payouts to sub (guest suite, elevator move clean, garbage deep clean, bio cleanup)
  - After-hours premium
  - Minimum call-out (maintenance)
- Include rules: travel included within X km; extra travel requires approval; no surprise charges.

E) SOPs (write like aviation checklists + decision trees)
SOP_01 Common Area Cleaning
- Step-by-step order of operations; must include safety, signage, tools, cleaning chemicals, "start-to-finish route," and required photos.
- Include "definition of done" per area.
SOP_02 Access & Conduct
- How to enter; what to do if denied access; resident interaction rules; escalations; prohibited behaviors.
SOP_03 Completion Proof
- Exactly how photos are taken, labeled, uploaded; minimum photos by area; what happens if missing; time stamping expectations.
SOP_04 Issue Escalation
- Categories: safety hazard, biohazard, property damage, vandalism, overflow garbage, water leak. Provide response steps and when to call admin.
SOP_05 Add-ons
- How to execute each add-on consistently; checklist and photo set.
SOP_06 Light Maintenance Workflow
- Define "will do/won't do"; triage; quoting; when to dispatch handyman; documentation; client approval; invoice/payout.

F) POLICIES (tight, enforceable internal rules)
Quality Standard & Rework
- Pass/fail thresholds; how rework is assigned; when subs are removed from a site; how credits are decided; recordkeeping.
Health & Safety
- PPE, chemicals, slips; incident reporting; no needles/bio unless trained; stop-work authority.
Privacy & Photos
- No resident faces; no unit doors with numbers visible if avoidable; storage rules; retention period.
Subcontractor Conduct
- No solicitation, no pricing talk, no gifts; no social media; professionalism.
Communications
- Only admin communicates with client; subs communicate only with admin.
Billing & Collections
- Monthly in advance; service holds; add-on approvals; dispute handling timeline.

G) QA FORMS (templates)
- Each form must include: required fields, checkboxes, pass/fail, signature blocks, timestamps.
- QA_01 Site Inspection: include scoring (0–100), defect list, corrective action, re-inspection date.
- QA_05 Monthly Summary: visits completed, issues, add-ons, notes for board.

H) CHECKLIST LIBRARY
- Each checklist: tasks, frequency guidance, photo points, "fail conditions."
- Ensure they can be imported into a portal later: stable IDs for each checklist item (e.g., LOB-001).

I) STATE MACHINES & ROLES
- Define roles: ADMIN, OPS_MANAGER (optional), SUBCONTRACTOR.
- Define entity states and transitions:
  - Job: Scheduled → Completed Pending Approval → Approved Payable → Paid / Cancelled
  - Work Order: Requested → Approved → Assigned → Completed → Invoiced → Paid
  - Invoice: Draft → Issued → Paid / Overdue
  - Payout: Calculated → Approved → Released → Paid
- Audit log: every transition stored with actor, timestamps, metadata.

J) SALES ENABLEMENT
- Discovery script specifically for property managers (complaints, scope, frequency, decision process, current vendor pain).
- Site walk checklist: what to measure/observe; how to estimate frequency; risk areas.
- Proposal insert: explain QA accountability in 1 page.

OUTPUT QUALITY BAR
- Use professional legal/ops tone, concise but complete.
- No contradictions across docs.
- Define key terms once and reuse.
- Make sure client contract and sub contract align on: proof requirements, scope boundaries, and communications boundaries.

